juniTacacsPlusClientMIB.name: juniTacacsPlusClientMIB

revisions.description: Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniTacacsPlusClientMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniTacacsPlusClientMIB.description: The Terminal Access Controller Access Control System Plus (TACACS+) Client MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

JuniKeyString.name: JuniKeyString
JuniKeyString.description: A string to keep a TACACS+ key. It may contain TAB character and/or any character from 0x20 to 0x7e inclusive. Its lenght is limited to 100. For security reasons it always reads as an empty string.

juniTacacsPlusClientDirectedRequest.name: juniTacacsPlusClientDirectedRequest
juniTacacsPlusClientDirectedRequest.description: This object represents directed-request option setting. In any of the enabled enabled states user name entered as `user@host' will be sent to specified host fot authentication. If `restricted' is in effect and the specified host is not available client would not try to use other hosts, if `truncated' is in effect, then `@host' part will be stripped before submission for authentication.

juniTacacsPlusClientTimeout.name: juniTacacsPlusClientTimeout
juniTacacsPlusClientTimeout.description: TACACS+ host response timeout in seconds. Value 0 means 'not configured, it this case built-in internal timeout value will be used.

juniTacacsPlusClientKey.name: juniTacacsPlusClientKey
juniTacacsPlusClientKey.description: If the size is non-zero, packets passed between host and client will be encrypted.

juniTacacsPlusClientSourceIp.name: juniTacacsPlusClientSourceIp
juniTacacsPlusClientSourceIp.description: If the value is is not 0.0.0.0 client will use this address as a source IP address for communication with servers. Changing this value would not affect existing connections.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigTable.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigTable
juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigTable.description: This table contains per host configuration parameters.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigEntry.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigEntry
juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigEntry.description: A TACACS+ host statistics table entry.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAddr.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAddr
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAddr.description: The IP address of the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostPort.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostPort
juniTacacsPlusClientHostPort.description: The TCP port of the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostPrimary.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostPrimary
juniTacacsPlusClientHostPrimary.description: Non-directed requests are submitted to the primary host first. There is only one primary host in the table. So, setting this object to true, will also change the value of this object in the current primary host. If primary host is deleted or reset, system will assing new primary host. When the first entry is created it becomes primary regardless of the value of this object.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostSingleConnection.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostSingleConnection
juniTacacsPlusClientHostSingleConnection.description: Traditionally TACACS+ client creates a new TCP connection for every session. If this value is true then TACACS+ client will try to use single connection if supported both by client implementation and by the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostTimeout.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostTimeout
juniTacacsPlusClientHostTimeout.description: TACACS+ host response timeout in seconds. If the value is 0 then the value of juniTacacsPlusClientTimeout will be used instead.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostKey.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostKey
juniTacacsPlusClientHostKey.description: If size is non-zero, packets passed between host and client will be encrypted with the key, otherwise the value of juniTacacsPlusClientKey will be used for the purpose.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatus.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatus
juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatus.description: Status object, only `createAndGo' and 'destroy' are supported.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostOrder.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostOrder
juniTacacsPlusClientHostOrder.description: The search order of this TACACS+ host within all configured TACACS+ hosts. This MIB object indicates the order in which a TACACS+ request will be sent to the TACACS+ hosts until a response is received. The primary host is always the first host to be contacted. The remaining hosts will be contacted in the order that they were created. Should the primary host be deleted, the next host in the search order will become the primary host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatsTable.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatsTable
juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatsTable.description: This table contains per host statistics.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatsEntry.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatsEntry
juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatsEntry.description: A TACACS+ host statistics table entry.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthRequests.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthRequests
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthRequests.description: Number of authentication requests sent to the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthReplies.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthReplies
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthReplies.description: Number of authentication replies received from the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthPending.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthPending
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthPending.description: Number of expected but not received authentication replies from the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthTimeouts.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthTimeouts
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthTimeouts.description: Number of authentication timeouts for the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorRequests.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorRequests
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorRequests.description: Number of authorization requests sent to the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorReplies.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorReplies
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorReplies.description: Number of authorization replies received from the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorPending.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorPending
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorPending.description: Number of expected but not received authorization replies from the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorTimeouts.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorTimeouts
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAuthorTimeouts.description: Number of authorization timeouts for the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctRequests.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctRequests
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctRequests.description: Number of accounting requests sent to the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctReplies.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctReplies
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctReplies.description: Number of accounting replies received from the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctPending.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctPending
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctPending.description: Number of expected but not received accounting replies from the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctTimeouts.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctTimeouts
juniTacacsPlusClientHostAcctTimeouts.description: Number of accounting timeouts for the host.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostDiscontinuityTim.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostDiscontinuityTime
juniTacacsPlusClientHostDiscontinuityTim.description: The value of sysUpTime when corresponding juniTacacsPlusHostConfigEntry was created, this object containg zero if host entry was created during system initializatin.

juniTacacsPlusCompliance.name: juniTacacsPlusCompliance
juniTacacsPlusCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper TACACS+ Client MIB.

juniTacacsPlusCompliance2.name: juniTacacsPlusCompliance2
juniTacacsPlusCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Juniper TACACS+ Client MIB.

juniTacacsPlusClientCommonGroup.name: juniTacacsPlusClientCommonGroup
juniTacacsPlusClientCommonGroup.description: This group defines common configuration parameters for all hosts.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigGroup.name: juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigGroup
juniTacacsPlusClientHostConfigGroup.description: Obsolete group for defining per host configuration parameters.

juniTacacsPlusClientHostStatsGroup.description: This group defines statistics collected on per host basis.
